# Vue 3 and Tailwind-specific rules
language: vue
framework: vue3
styling: tailwind

# General coding principles
principles:
  - Write clear, concise code
  - Adhere to Vue 3 and Tailwind best practices
  - Implement incremental changes
  - Consider potential side effects
  - Be aware of installed packages in package.json

# Specific rules
rules:
  - Prefer composition API over options API
  - Use script setup syntax when appropriate
  - Utilize Vue 3 reactivity system (ref, reactive, computed)
  - Implement proper component structure and naming conventions
  - Optimize performance with Vue 3 features (e.g., v-memo, Suspense)
  - Use Tailwind utility classes for styling
  - Avoid inline styles unless necessary
  - Implement proper state management (Pinia preferred over Vuex)
  - Use async/await for asynchronous operations
  - Implement proper error handling and logging
  - Ensure proper typing with TypeScript when used
  - Utilize Vue 3 Teleport for modals and popups
  - Implement accessibility features (ARIA attributes, semantic HTML)

# Refactoring guidelines
refactoring:
  - Suggest incremental improvements
  - Identify and address potential side effects
  - Consider impact on existing functionality
  - Optimize for readability and maintainability
  - Ensure backward compatibility when possible

# Package awareness
packages:
  - Verify compatibility with Vue 3 and Tailwind
  - Suggest alternatives for deprecated or incompatible packages
  - Recommend removal of unused packages
  - Propose new packages only when significant benefits are evident

# Code quality
quality:
  - Implement proper unit and integration testing
  - Ensure consistent code formatting (use Prettier or ESLint)
  - Maintain appropriate component granularity
  - Optimize imports and remove unused code
  - Use meaningful variable and function names

# Performance
performance:
  - Implement lazy loading for routes and components
  - Optimize rendering with v-once and v-memo when appropriate
  - Minimize unnecessary re-renders
  - Implement proper caching strategies
  - Optimize asset loading and management
